When a carbonated drink was poured onto a car window, the glass shattered instantly. But strangely, when this man did the same to his own car, the glass remained completely intact. In reality, a carbonated drink isn‚Äôt strong enough to break car glass, as its pressure is too weak. The real reason the glass shattered wasn't the soda itself, but a small pre-existing crack in the glass. When the cold soda was poured, the low temperature and carbonation pressure accelerated the spread of the crack‚Äîcausing the glass to break apart.
